The paper deals with the information complexity of learning algorithms, which is a topic that falls under the broad category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the concept of VC-dimension, which is a measure of the complexity of a hypothesis class, and is closely related to information theory (cs.IT). The paper uses probabilistic arguments and explores the average case complexity of learning, which suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of data structures (cs.DS) and computational complexity (cs.CC). Finally, the paper proposes a low-information learning algorithm, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
